HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 230
By Russell
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Melanie Sloan on her
receipt of the Governor's Volunteer Stars Award.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those estimable citizens who have dedicated their time and energies to helping
others; and
WHEREAS, each year, 1.3 million Tennessee volunteers give over 99 million hours of
community service, contributing $2.6 billion to Tennessee's economy; and
WHEREAS, these volunteers are the backbone of our communities, and by donating
their time and talents to fulfill needs that would otherwise go unmet, they embody the spirit of
giving; and
WHEREAS, Melanie Sloan of Monroe County is one such exemplary person, who is a
recipient of the Governor's Volunteer Stars Award in recognition of her laudable commitment to
her community; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Sloan, a devoted resident of Madisonville, dedicated hundreds of hours
of planning, promoting, and organizing to secure a common commitment among the varied
stakeholders of the Downtown Madisonville Alliance to revitalize the Madisonville city center;
and
WHEREAS, Ms. Sloan, using all the tools at her disposal, formed partnerships with local
businesses and organized community events to secure the project's viability and success, while
always promoting a preservation-based development that protected the beloved identity of the
city; and
